# Stock-Em

HEROKU LIVE LINK: https://stockem-0caaa6588e50.herokuapp.com/welcome/index

Code Climate Report : https://codeclimate.com/github/LOGiC31/Stock-Em

Capstone Inventory Management System - A smart way of managing your inventories.



1. **How to get started with development  **
1. Clone the repo using https or ssh
   git clone <https://github.com/LOGiC31/Stock-Em.git>

	OR

	git clone <git@github.com>:LOGiC31/Stock-Em.git

1. Run cd Stock-Em to get into the directory.
1. Run *bundle install*

   You will get the below error message when you run *bundle install* command

   ![](data:image/png;base64,)

   So, run this command first: 

	   bundle install --without 'production' ;

   then run *bundle install* again.

1. Run *rails db:drop*
1. Run *rails db:create*
1. Run *rails db:migrate*
1. Run *rails db:seed*
1. Run *rails server*
1. **How to run the tests**
1. Ensure Test Dependencies Are Installed:
   *bundle install*

1. Prepare the Test Database:
   *rails db:test:prepare*

1. Run RSpec Tests:
   *bundle exec rspec*

1. Run Cucumber Tests:
   *bundle exec cucumber*
   // A browser window opens for validating a few scenarios in real time.

1. View Test Coverage :
   Open the *open coverage/index.html* file in your browser:
1. **How to get the application deployed**

- **Login into your heroku(using CLI):**

		heroku login

- **Create a heroku application**

		heroku create <app-name>

- **Initialize a git repo (If not initialized)**

		git init
		git add .
		git commit -m "Initial commit"

- Follow these steps to initialize Postgres for your application in heroku dashboard 
	1. Go to resources of application and search for add on ‘Heroku Postgres’.
	2. Select ‘Heroku Postgres’ from the list and add it to your application.
	
	![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- **Push the project to heroku ‘main’ branch**

								git push heroku master:main
**			  ![](data:image/png;base64,)

- **Run db:migration on heroku**

		heroku run rake db:migrate

- **Seed starter data on heroku**

		heroku run rake db:seed
		
- **Run your application**

		heroku open
